This map is amazing. Not just because of it's beautiful ambiance, smooth walls, or glowing boxes, but because it has a shitload (it's an imperial unit) of brushes. This map uses fully 86% of Hammer's brush capacity. Let me tell you why: because it knows you want it. This map knows you've been longing to touch and caress its smooth curves, to brush your lips on its glowing stripes, and to maybe, just maybe, give it a handjob in the back room of a 7-11.

Other than the immense sexual fantasy you just had, the map has all the typical stuff. 
Built for gameplay, optimized for shitty computers, and dressed up all fancy just for you.

Let me know what you think. It's not hard, just type it in the little box down there. I'll get back to you with some nudie pics and a bottle of lotion.

UNTIL I COME AGAIN!

-bclose

Look at that pretty neon map! OH MAN. I just want to rub that purple brushwork all over my body and lay naked in a bathtub with it. A soapy bathtub. With hot, hot water. If you catch my drift. So it's another smooth neon map by me, bclose. It is purple because I wanted to move more into warm colors with the pink/purple instead of doing another cool colored one. The next might be red, then orange, then yellow. I'll probably end up doing the whole spectrum eventually. Dear Krusty, no I did not use your tutorial. I can do this from memory now. KTHANKS.

Here's a second in a possible series of "smooth" maps I've made. Only a few sharp corners and nice neon lighting to finish off the smooth, clean visual effect I like in my gungame maps. Since the last one was blue, I wanted to go with a different color, but warm colors seemed to make the map a little more hostile, while the green was a nice medium color with a little edge to it.

There are buyzones. Gungame turns them off, I believe. If not, I guess you can buy stuff.

In the next version there will be monster truck sounds. Maybe.

My first build:  a disorienting platform in space.
Two versions (GG_SMEARE3 and GG_SMEARENIGHT) are included.
SMEARE has a clearer visual display,
but SMARENIGHT has a nice display of dim lighting.


- Not compatible with bots.  Some of them run off the edge and fall indefinitely.
- The smearing effect only applies to empty space, so it's not complete visual chaos.

This is my first non-symmetrical map attempt. I can't quite make out if I like this map, or not. It's a very strange map.

This map has buy zones, thus does not have to be played as a gungame map.

There's a "dark room" to the right of the ct spawn. Can be a fun place for knife fights.

This map has buyzones, so that it can be played as a gungame map, or as an aim/fy map. About This Map I was rather inspired when I saw someone's dev textured version of their map ( http://farm1.static.flickr.com/186/394525257_fc10adc481.jpg ). I liked it a lot, so I copied the idea. Then I took the curve idea maps like gg_circular. When I first created this map, I didn't think it would work out at all. It works much better than I imagined! The blue color from my custom textures comes from the Tango Project icon palette.

This map is a complete remake of gg_prisoncompound (I did not create gg_prisoncompound). I liked the idea of the map, but the textures were screwy, and it had too many props. So I completely recreated it (not modified it) to suit my liking. This map is a much cleaner version of gg_prisoncompound with my own twists.

This map has buy zones, thus does not have to be played as a gungame map.

This is a newer version of my gg_sl_cross2 map. The skybox has been changed (it still needs a 3d skybox), slightly altered lighting (brightness), and added section to the right of each spawn to give players more variety. It also has 32 spawn points. Many of the textures have been fixed. This is probably my favorite map of all my creations. It can also be played as a gungame map or as an AIM map (has buyzones).

This is my second map; the first being this map with only the cross center piece.

As I recall, I added 12 spawns on each side. The map does not play well as a deathmatch map due to the spawn locations, unless they are modified.

Edit: I believe the map is using skyboxes. However, after compiling another build today, I realized there was an issue with skyboxes and hdr (which I removed).

Edit 2: Here's the latest build of gg_sl_cross3: (redacted).
In this map, I changed the skybox, slightly altered lighting (brightness), and added a part to the map to give players more variety. (And added more spawn points--16 on each side.) I would like to add moving clouds, and maybe some other spice.
